<item>
            <title>[MNG-2234] activeProfile in ~/.m2/settings.xml is ignored when profiles section is missing or empty</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MNG-2234</link>
                <project id="12316922" key="MNG">Maven (Moved to GitHub Issues)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When i have this settings.xml file in my user home dir, the activeProfile setting is simply ignored by Maven:&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;settings&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
 &amp;lt;activeProfiles&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
     &amp;lt;activeProfile&amp;gt;env-test&amp;lt;/activeProfile&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
 &amp;lt;/activeProfiles&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;/settings&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Adding an empty profiles section does not help:&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;settings&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
 &amp;lt;profiles&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
 &amp;lt;/profiles&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
 &amp;lt;activeProfiles&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
     &amp;lt;activeProfile&amp;gt;env-test&amp;lt;/activeProfile&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
 &amp;lt;/activeProfiles&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;/settings&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Well, adding a dummy profile makes it work:&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;settings&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
 &amp;lt;profiles&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;profile&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
          &amp;lt;id&amp;gt;dummy&amp;lt;/id&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;/profile&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
 &amp;lt;/profiles&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
 &amp;lt;activeProfiles&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
     &amp;lt;activeProfile&amp;gt;env-test&amp;lt;/activeProfile&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
 &amp;lt;/activeProfiles&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;/settings&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Funny, isn&apos;t it?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Regards,&lt;br/&gt;
Manfred&lt;/p&gt;</description>
